// Title
#text(size: 18pt, weight: "bold")[Data Usage Agreement]




#v(0.5em)

This Data Usage Agreement ("Agreement") governs the access to and use of the Hamburg Fluctuating Pain Database ("Database"). The Database is released under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC-BY-4.0). By downloading or otherwise accessing the Database, the User agrees to be bound by the terms of this Agreement and the CC-BY-4.0 license.

#line(length: 100%, stroke: 0.5pt)

#v(0.3em)

// Section 1
#text(weight: "bold")[1. Acceptance of Terms]

#v(0.5em)

By downloading or otherwise accessing the Database, the User acknowledges that they have read, understood, and agreed to comply with all terms and conditions of this Agreement. Access to the Database is conditional upon acceptance of these terms. This Agreement may be terminated by either party at any time, but the User's obligations with respect to the Database shall continue after termination.

#v(0.8em)

// Section 2
#text(weight: "bold")[2. Permitted Use and Restrictions]

#v(0.5em)

The User agrees to the following conditions regarding the use of the Database:
- Purpose: The Database shall be used restrictively for internal, lawful scientific research and analysis purposes only.
- No Re-identification: The User will not attempt to identify or re-identify any individual participant referenced in the Database, either directly or via cross-reference with other sources.
- No Redistribution: The User will not share access to or re-distribute the Database to any other individual or entity not specifically named or signed in the agreement. All users must obtain the data directly. Sharing analysis outputs and derivatives does not breach this clause, provided there is no external interaction with participants or exposure of restricted raw data.
- Security: The User promises to exercise all reasonable and prudent care to host and manage the data securely, maintaining appropriate physical and electronic security controls and necessary training.

#v(0.8em)

// Section 3
#text(weight: "bold")[3. Incident Reporting]

#v(0.5em)

If the User suspects a data breach or discovers information within the Database that they believe might permit the identification of any participant, the User agrees to report the incident and the location of this specific information promptly to the dataset providers.

#v(0.8em)

// Section 4
#text(weight: "bold")[4. Intellectual Property]

#v(0.5em)

This Agreement does not add to or remove any intellectual property protections inherently held by the dataset. The Database remains licensed under the aforementioned CC-BY-4.0 open license.

#v(0.8em)

// Section 5
#text(weight: "bold")[5. Disclaimer of Warranty and Limitation of Liability]

#v(0.5em)

The Database is provided "as is," without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of accuracy, completeness, or fitness for a particular purpose. The University Medical Center Hamburg-Eppendorf shall not be held liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use or inability to use the Database.

#v(0.8em)

// Section 6
#text(weight: "bold")[6. Citation Requirement]

#v(0.5em)

Any publication, presentation, or other work reporting on the use or stemming from the results of the Database must include a proper citation to the following paper, which provides a comprehensive description of the Database:

